  "day": 56,
  "key": "day_56_triumphal_entry",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-17",
  "title": {
    "en": "The King Enters Jerusalem"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "After raising Lazarus, Jesus traveled to Jerusalem for the Feast.",
      "A great crowd gathered to welcome him."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "crowd",
        "icon": "celebration",
        "label": { "en": "Hosanna!" },
        "lines": [
          "The crowd took palm branches",
          "and went out to meet him.",
          "They shouted,",
          "“Hosanna!”",
          "“Blessed is he who comes",
          "in the name of the Lord!”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "king",
        "icon": "emoji_events",
        "label": { "en": "Your King Is Coming" },
        "lines": [
          "Jesus found a young donkey",
          "and sat upon it,",
          "as it is written:",
          "“Do not be afraid,",
          "O Daughter of Zion;",
          "see, your king is coming,",
          "seated on a donkey’s colt.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "understanding",
        "icon": "lightbulb",
        "label": { "en": "Written About Him" },
        "lines": [
          "At first his disciples did not understand.",
          "Only later did they realize",
          "that these things had been written about him,",
          "and that they had done these things to him."
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "Why would a king enter a city on a donkey instead of a war horse? What kind of king is being presented here?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["John 12:12–16"]
  }
}
